  <p>Welcome to ECS, the School of Electronics and Computer Science at the University of Southampton. ECS is one of the world's leading centres for research, teaching, enterprise and innovation in Electronics, Electrical Engineering and Computer Science.</p>

  <h2>Serious Fire</h2>
<img src="http://ia360911.us.archive.org:9090/wayback/20051104013851im_/http://www.ecs.soton.ac.uk/fire2005/mbtn.jpg" alt="" style="float: right; margin-left:1em;border:solid 1px black;margin-bottom:1em" />
<p>On Sunday 30th October a major fire at the Universityâ€™s Highfield Campus has partially destroyed the Mountbatten Building, in particular the area containing the Silicon Fabrication Facility. Fortunately, no-one was injured or is missing as a result of the fire.</p>


<h2>
School of Electronics and Computer Science: 
Guidance from the School</h2>

<h3>ECS Meeting</h3>

<p>Friday 4 November<br />
3.30pm Garden Court<br />
University Staff Social Centre<br />
An opportunity for all ECS staff and research students to get together.</p>

<ul>  
<li>update on current situation </li>
<li>followed by drinks and snacks </li>
 </ul>

<p>We hope to see you all there! </p>

